  {
    "Name": "Goin'…Gone",
    "Author": "Lisa Wesley",
    "Year": 1999,
    "Type": "performance",
    "Material": "",
    "Dimensions": "(53 min 41s)",
    "Series": "",
    "Description": "Lisa Wesley’s piece Goin...Gone took place in a space strewn with thousands\nof copies of pages from a five-act play (complete with character names\nand stage directions). Sitting at a pub table and drinking a pint of her own\npiss she performed, almost to herself, the given drama (which was a kind of\nTim Etchells-esque narrative about Saturday night lowlife in pursuit of sex,\noblivion and redemption) over and over and over again. But at each point in\nthe cycle of repetition her body became increasing absorbed by/immersed\nin the narrative - the texts become concrete as she literally consumed all the\npeanuts, crisps, condoms and piss that are the trappings of a night out in any\nBritish city. She scrawled fragments of the text onto herself and sellotaped\npages of the manuscript all over her body until she literally disappeared into\nit.\n(https://www.thisisliveart.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/BodilyFunctions_Final-copy.pdf)",
    "Image Link": "https://www.thisisliveart.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/uploads/documents/Bodily_Functions_In_Performance_SRG.pdf",
    "path extension": "piss-images/",
    "image file name": "goin-gone_wesley.jpg",
    "@image": "assets/img/piss-images/goin-gone_wesley.jpg",
    "extra images/videos for website": "",
    "notes": "video/ more info?"
  },
